x4freetext: the Elbek-type multiangle spectrograph.
The tritons were detected in Ilford L4 nuclear
emulsions. Aluminium absorbers varying in thickness
were placed directly before the nuclear emulsions to
reduce the triton energy to give optimum ionization in
the nuclear emulsions
2 mm silicon surface-barrier monitor detector
The targets were produced by evaporating enriched
isotopes with purities 99.2% Sm-152, 95.5% Sm-150 and
96.4% Sm-148 onto carbon backings. The target
thicknesses varied between 150 and 200 mug/cm**2
and the thickness of the backings was about
. An absolute cross sections scale was
established to +-20% by measuring the proton elastic
scattering on each target in separate short
spectrograph exposures at the beginning of each run.
